English Premier League 2019-08-24 Watford vs West Ham
column7: Pre-season has not had the cleansing effect Watford would have hoped. The blistering downward spiral of results from the end of last season has bled into this. Javi Gracia needs a spark and Ismala Sarrs defence-shredding pace could be exactly that if he makes his debut. West Ham will hope Sbastian Haller is fit to return and able to capitalise on any fragility that two defeats and no goals has engendered at Vicarage Road. Add Watford missing Troy Deeneys leadership and you start to feel slightly nervous for Gracia. (The Guardian)

column3: English Premier League 2019-08-24 Brighton vs Southampton
column7: Southampton lost their opening two matches but tend to be tricky opposition for Brighton and will surely fancy their chances after Graham Potters attacking revolution stalled against West Ham. Kevin Danso could also debut to refresh Ralph Hassenhttls defence  a unit that kept Liverpool in check for long periods last time out. The workout given to the backline should have them prepared to stifle Potters plans for keeping the good times rolling at the Amex. (The Guardian)

column3: English Premier League 2019-08-24 Liverpool vs Arsenal
column7: Both teams have made a 100% start to the new season but it will require a first win at Anfield for seven years, or a rare display of substance at least, for the visitors credentials to be taken seriously. Arsenals last three visits to Liverpool have produced 5-1, 4-0 and 3-1 defeats. There was another 5-1 humiliation in 2014 after Arsne Wengers team started the day as Premier League leaders. Arsenals quality up front could test a Liverpool defence that has not quite recaptured last seasons form.(The Guardian)

column3: English Premier League 2019-08-24 Manchester United vs Crystal Palace
column7: After two matches the way Ole Gunnar Solskjr wants Manchester United to play is clear and he will hope this high-energy pressing game can break down Crystal Palace. Roy Hodgsons side lost at Sheffield United in their last match and are seeking to bounce back yet this is an opponent Solskjrs men will be disappointed not to beat at Old Trafford.(The Guardian)

column3: English Premier League 2019-08-24 Norwich vs Chelsea
column7: Daniel Farke found himself in the odd situation of having to play down expectations before Chelseas visit to Carrow Road. Listen, we spent less than 1m this summer, he said, Chelsea are the Europa League winners. We remain underdogs. That the German has to issue such a reminder is a reflection on the quality of Norwichs victory over Newcastle, but also the stuttering start of Frank Lampards side. There is more consternation for Lampard with the news that NGolo Kant is a doubt for the match, while Antonio Rdiger remains unavailable. Norwich look set to name an unchanged side.(The Guardian)

column3: English Premier League 2019-08-24 Sheffield United vs Leicester
column7: Sheffield United have enjoyed an impressive reintroduction to Premier League life but their manager, Chris Wilder, is rightly wary about the threat posed by Jamie Vardy. Like Wilder, Leicesters star striker, is from Sheffield and began his career in non-league circles but there is one key difference

column3: English Premier League 2019-08-25 Bournemouth vs Manchester City
column7: Can Bournemouth stop Manchester City? Probably not. Eight defeats from eight meetings in the Premier League speaks for itself. How Pep Guardiolas side respond to completely dominating Tottenham but failing to win is key. If profligacy is again the order of the day then Eddie Howe could spring a surprise. A rather large if, however, considering the embarrassment of talent at Guardiolas disposal.(The Guardian)

column3: English Premier League 2019-08-25 Wolves vs Burnley
column7: So far Wolves have combined domestic and European duties very impressively. Their squad has shown enough depth  thanks partly to Adama Traors terrific improvement  to suggest that Nuno Esprito Santo could make some alterations to the lineup that achieved an excellent win at Torino on Thursday and still be confident of securing a first Premier League win of the season. Burnley, however, will be troublesome visitors so this will be a serious test. (Paul Doyle-The Guardian)

column3: English Premier League 2019-08-25 Tottenham vs Newcastle
column7: Two games in and Steve Bruce feels backed into a corner. It was always going to be tough to take over from Rafael Bentez but the manner Newcastles defeat at Norwich appeared to crystalise the supporters worst fears. Where Bentezs team would be ferociously well drilled on the road, Bruces was picked apart. A result might be beyond Newcastle at Tottenham but signs of cohesion and attacking punch are urgently needed. (David Hytne- The Guardian)

column3: English Premier League 2019-08-31 Leicester vs Bournemouth
column7: Jamie Vardy scored twice and made the other as an impressive Leicester maintained their unbeaten Premier League start by easing past Bournemouth at King Power Stadium.

column3: English Premier League 2019-08-31 Manchester City vs Brighton
column7: Sergio Aguero was labelled a "special talent" by Manchester City boss Pep Guardiola after the Argentine hit two goals against Brighton, continuing his record of scoring in all four of his team's Premier League games this season.

column3: English Premier League 2019-08-31 Newcastle vs Watford
column7: Will Hughes' early goal helped Watford secure their first Premier League point of the season with a battling draw at Newcastle.

column3: English Premier League 2019-08-31 Burnley vs Liverpool
column7: Liverpool manager Jurgen Klopp played down striker Sadio Mane's reaction after being substituted in the 3-0 win at Burnley, and then praised his forward line for helping the club achieve a 13-match winning run in the Premier League.

column3: English Premier League 2019-08-31 Southampton vs Manchester United
column7: Jannik Vestergaard's towering header gave 10-man Southampton a point after another moment of magic from Manchester United new boy Daniel James looked to have put them on course for victory at St Mary's.

column3: English Premier League 2019-08-31 Chelsea vs Sheffield United
column7: Sheffield United manager Chris Wilder said his side are "not day trippers" after they battled back from two goals down to snatch a point at Stamford Bridge.

column3: English Premier League 2019-08-31 West Ham vs Norwich
column7: West Ham United boss Manuel Pellegrini says striker Sebastien Haller is a "complete player" after he scored a third goal in two games during their win against Norwich City.

column3: English Premier League 2019-08-31 Crystal Palace vs Aston Villa
column7: Roy Hodgson said his Crystal Palace side did not need to "apologise" for their 1-0 Premier League win over 10-man Aston Villa, after the visitors had a late equaliser controversially ruled out.

column3: English Premier League 2019-09-01 Everton vs Wolves
English Premier League 2019-09-01 Arsenal vs Tottenham
column7: Arsenal staged a stirring comeback to earn a point in a chaotic, thrilling north London derby against Tottenham at Emirates Stadium.

English Premier League 2019-10-25 Southampton vs Leicester
column7: Ben Chilwell opened the scoring in the 10th minute. Ryan Bertrand of Southampton was dismissed for a studs-up challenge in the build-up to the goal, confirmed by VAR, two minutes later. Leicester were 30 up by the 19th minute, thanks to Youri Tielemans and Ayoze Prez. Prez added the fourth on the 39th minute, with Jamie Vardy scoring on the stroke of half-time to send Leicester into the break ahead 50. Prez completed his hat-trick on the 57th minute, with Vardy adding his second and Leicester's seventh a minute later. James Maddison scored a 85th minute free-kick before Jamie Vardy completed his own hat-trick with a penalty four minutes into stoppage time. The final whistle blasted after the penalty was made. It was only the second time in Premier League history that two players scored a hat-trick for one team in the same game, last coming in an Arsenal 61 win over Southampton on 7 May 2003 with Jermaine Pennant and Robert Pires scoring three goals apiece.

column7: Exactly 100 days after the last game, Premier League soccer returns at Villa Park, where Aston Villa can climb out of the relegation zone with a win over Sheffield United. The Blades, meanwhile, would move into 5th with all three points.

column3: English Premier League 2020-06-17 Manchester City vs Arsenal
column7: The first day of Premier League action since March throws two English giants together as Mikel Arteta returns to Etihad Stadium. Arteta has overseen just one road win in the league since leaving Pep Guardiolas Manchester City to become Arsenal boss.

column3: English Premier League 2020-06-19 Norwich vs Southampton
column7: Having had three months to plot a great escape, Norwich City has its first opportunity to claw its way towards safety as Southampton - itself not yet clear of the drop - visits Carrow Road. Saints have lost just two of their last 14 against Norwich.

column3: English Premier League 2020-06-19 Tottenham vs Manchester United
column7: The battle for the UEFA Champions League returns in earnest as Jose Mourinho welcomes his former employer Manchester United to north London. Tottenham Hotspur fans will be glad to see soccer return, after a tumultuous period away from the field.

column3: English Premier League 2020-06-20 Watford vs Leicester
column7: Having run out 4-0 winner in the final game before the Premier League was halted, Leicester City is back in action, making the short trip to Vicarage Road to take on Watford. Brendan Rodgers team remains well-placed to secure a top-four finish.

column3: English Premier League 2020-06-20 Brighton vs Arsenal
column7: Among the most disappointing results of Arsenals season so far came at home to Graham Potters Brighton and Hove Albion, when Freddie Ljungberg was in charge. The Gunners now travel south for the reverse fixture, looking to avenge that 2-1 defeat.

column3: English Premier League 2020-06-20 West Ham vs Wolves
column7: Wolverhampton Wanderers - flying high before the break - restarts its season with a trip to face David Moyes West Ham United. The Hammers will hope to use the restart to their advantage, having won just one of their previous nine league games.

column3: English Premier League 2020-06-20 Bournemouth vs Crystal Palace
column7: Winless in four before the season was paused, Bournemouth is now looking to rediscover the form that saw it stun Chelsea in December. It welcomes a Crystal Palace team which is perhaps surprisingly closer to European qualification than relegation.

column7: With a place in Europe looking like an increasing possibility, Arsenal welcomes Premier League champion, Liverpool, to North London. The Gunners have not lost a game at Emirates Stadium since the Premier League's restart in June.

column3: English Premier League 2020-07-16 Everton vs Aston Villa
English Premier League 2020-07-16 Leicester vs Sheffield United
English Premier League 2020-07-16 Crystal Palace vs Manchester United
English Premier League 2020-07-16 Southampton vs Brighton
English Premier League 2020-07-17 West Ham vs Watford
English Premier League 2020-07-18 Norwich vs Burnley
English Premier League 2020-07-19 Bournemouth vs Southampton
English Premier League 2020-07-19 Tottenham vs Leicester
column7: Tottenham Hotspur and Leicester City go head-to-head as the race for Europe reaches its climax. James Maddison's late goal handed another damaging defeat to Mauricio Pochettino last September, while Brendan Rodgers meets old foe, Jose Mourinho.

column3: English Premier League 2020-07-20 Brighton vs Newcastle
English Premier League 2020-07-20 Sheffield United vs Everton
English Premier League 2020-07-20 Wolves vs Crystal Palace
English Premier League 2020-07-21 Watford vs Manchester City
English Premier League 2020-07-21 Aston Villa vs Arsenal
English Premier League 2020-07-22 Manchester United vs West Ham
English Premier League 2020-07-22 Liverpool vs Chelsea
column7: Liverpool's 2013/14 title challenge all-but ended after a home defeat to Chelsea. Six years later, Jurgen Klopp's rampant Reds have already sealed the title this time around, and will lift the Premier League trophy at the conclusion of this game.

column3: English Premier League 2020-07-26 Arsenal vs Watford
column7: Arsenal, unable to qualify for Europe through the league, hosts Watford on the final day of the season. While there's nothing resting on the game for the host, Watford needs at least a point and favourable results elsewhere to guarantee its safety.

column3: English Premier League 2020-07-26 Burnley vs Brighton
column7: Brighton and Hove Albion hopes to record its first Premier League win against Burnley as the season draws to a close. The Seagulls were moments away from achieving just that in the reverse fixture, before Jeff Hendrick scored a last-minute equalizer.

column3: English Premier League 2020-07-26 Chelsea vs Wolves
column7: Chelsea hosts Wolverhampton Wanderers at Stamford Bridge with the Premier League's finishing line in sight. Both can qualify for Europe but each needs a win to guarantee its place, so expect fireworks as both teams go for the win.

column3: English Premier League 2020-07-26 Crystal Palace vs Tottenham
column7: January 2015 was the last time Crystal Palace managed to score a Premier League goal against Tottenham Hotspur in the Premier League. Can Spurs win a 10th-consecutive contest over Palace or will the Eagles finally end their terrible run?

column3: English Premier League 2020-07-26 Everton vs Bournemouth
column7: Bournemouth's battle to stay in the Premier League reaches a climax as it travels to Everton on the final day of the season. Eddie Howe's team needs to win and hope that both Watford and Aston Villa lose to have any chance of survival.

column3: English Premier League 2020-07-26 Leicester vs Manchester United
column7: A spot in next season's UEFA Champions League is the prize as Leicester City and Manchester United square off. It's the away team that is in control as Ole Gunnar Solskjaer's men know that avoiding defeat will be enough to confirm their place.

column3: English Premier League 2020-07-26 Manchester City vs Norwich
column7: Norwich City's sensational 3-2 win over Manchester City last September was an early sign of the inconsistency that cost Pep Guardiola's team the title. The Canaries hope to give some cheer to their fans before returning to the EFL Championship.

column3: English Premier League 2020-07-26 Newcastle vs Liverpool
column7: Liverpool's historic season ends against Newcastle United at St James' Park. Georginio Wijnaldum scored against his future club when Newcastle beat Liverpool 2-0 in 2015, but the Reds have won the last four Premier League meetings between the pair.

column3: English Premier League 2020-07-26 Southampton vs Sheffield United
column7: Sheffield United and Southampton meet on the final day of the season, with the visitor having dropped out of contention for a UEFA Europa League spot. The Blades failed to beat Southampton in the reverse fixture at Bramall Lane, falling 1-0.

column3: English Premier League 2020-07-26 West Ham vs Aston Villa
column7: Two teams that have spent the season battling relegation meet on the final day as West Ham United hosts Aston Villa at London Stadium. Villa needs to better the result of both Bournemouth and Watford to maintain its Premier League status.

column3: English Premier League 2020-09-12 Crystal Palace vs Southampton
column7: Crystal Palace and Southampton collide on the opening weekend of the new Premier League season. The two performed very differently after last season's restart, with Southampton one of the most in-form teams, while Palace lost seven of its last eight.

column3: English Premier League 2020-09-12 Fulham vs Arsenal
column7: Newly-promoted Fulham's Premier League adventure begins with a London derby against Arsenal at Craven Cottage. Mikel Arteta begins his first full season in charge of the Gunners and has bolstered his squad by signing Willian from Chelsea.

column3: English Premier League 2020-09-12 Liverpool vs Leeds
column7: Leeds United faces a big test on its long-awaited return to the Premier League as it takes on defending champion, Liverpool. Jurgen Klopp's men are well-rested, unlike other title contenders, as they didn't play the UEFA Champions League in August.

column3: English Premier League 2020-09-12 West Ham vs Newcastle
column7: After spending much of last season battling relegation, West Ham United and Newcastle United begin the new season in search of a fresh start. The Magpies continue life under long-term owner Mike Ashley after their proposed offseason sale fell through.

column3: English Premier League 2020-09-13 Tottenham vs Everton
column7: Two titans of world soccer collide on the opening weekend as Jose Mourinho's Tottenham Hotspur takes on Carlo Ancelotti's Everton. Spurs striker Harry Kane has an impressive record against Everton, scoring nine goals in 10 games.

column3: English Premier League 2020-09-13 West Brom vs Leicester
column7: Reigning Premier League Golden Boot winner Jamie Vardy looks to make a fast start to the season as Leicester City heads on the road to face newly-promoted West Bromwich Albion. The Foxes are aiming to build on last season's superb 5th-place finish.

column3: English Premier League 2020-09-14 Brighton vs Chelsea
column7: Graham Potters Brighton and Hove Albion avoided relegation last season with a steely resilience to not be beaten. Such durability was showcased against Chelsea at AMEX Stadium as Alireza Jahanbakhshs bicycle kick secured a point for the Seagulls.

column3: English Premier League 2020-09-14 Sheffield United vs Wolves
column7: Sheffield United and Wolverhampton Wanderers begin their season by going head-to-head at Bramall Lane. Both teams were in the hunt for European qualification for most of last season but missed out after falling away in the final couple of weeks.

column3: English Premier League 2020-09-19 Arsenal vs West Ham
column7: An all-London clash at Emirates Stadium as Arsenal hosts West Ham United. Gunners boss Mikel Arteta is looking to build on a successful first nine months in charge, which saw his team win the FA Cup and Community Shield in the last two months.

column3: English Premier League 2020-09-19 Everton vs West Brom
column7: Everton faces newly-promoted West Bromwich Albion at Goodison Park. After a disappointing 12th-place finish last season, Carlo Ancelotti will be looking to get his team back in the top half of tha table and secure a European qualification spot.

column3: English Premier League 2020-09-19 Leeds vs Fulham
English Premier League 2020-09-19 Manchester United vs Crystal Palace
column7: Manchester United gets its 2020/21 Premier League campaign underway against Crystal Palace at Old Trafford. The Red Devils have bolstered their ranks during the transfer window with the signing of Dutch midfielder Donny van de Beek.

column3: English Premier League 2020-09-20 Chelsea vs Liverpool
column7: Liverpool heads on the road to face Chelsea in the first major test of its Premier League title defence. Its trophy presentation last season took place after a gripping 5-3 victory over Chelsea, which included a goal from Christian Pulisic.

column3: English Premier League 2020-09-20 Leicester vs Burnley
column7: Burnley travels to Leicester City in the first away game of its 2020/21 Premier League campaign. Sean Dyche's team finished 10th last season and will be looking to challenge for a UEFA Europa League spot this time around.

column3: English Premier League 2020-09-20 Newcastle vs Brighton
column7: Brighton and Hove Albion makes the long trip to the north of England to face Newcastle United at St. James' Park. New signings Callum Wilson and Jeff Hendrick have hit the ground running for Newcastle, both scoring on matchday one.

column3: English Premier League 2020-09-20 Southampton vs Tottenham
column7: Southampton welcomes Jose Mourinho's Tottenham Hotspur to St Mary's Stadium. Saints fans will hope that star striker Danny Ings can replicate his form from last season, which saw him finish second in the race for the Premier League Golden Boot.

column3: English Premier League 2020-09-21 Aston Villa vs Sheffield United
column7: After securing top-flight survival on the final day, Aston Villa begins its 2020/21 Premier League campaign against Sheffield United. The Blades are seeking revenge after goal-line technology robbed Chris Wilder's team of a win at Villa Park in July.

column3: English Premier League 2020-09-21 Wolves vs Manchester City
column7: Manchester City's Premier League season finally gets underway as it takes on Wolverhampton Wanderers. City failed to beat Wolves in both matches last year, with the latter overcoming a two-goal deficit to win 3-2 in a thriller at Molineux.

column3: English Premier League 2020-09-26 Brighton vs Manchester United
column7: Ole Gunnar Solskjaer's Manchester United heads on the road for the first time this Premier League season as it takes on Brighton and Hove Albion. Instrumental midfielder Bruno Fernandes scored a brace in a 3-0 win when United last visited in June.

column3: English Premier League 2020-09-26 Burnley vs Southampton
column7: Two English strikers come up against their former teams as Danny Ings' Southampton visits Jay Rodriguez's Burnley at Turf Moor. Ings scored one of his 22 Premier League goals last season against Burnley, as the Clarets won 2-1 at St Mary's.

column3: English Premier League 2020-09-26 Crystal Palace vs Everton
column7: Crystal Palace and Everton meet at Selhurst Park in the Premier League. Everton's midfield has been revamped over the summer, with the introduction of James Rodriguez, Allan and Abdoulaye Doucoure providing a new look to Carlo Ancelotti's team.

column3: English Premier League 2020-09-26 West Brom vs Chelsea
column7: The Hawthorns opens its doors to Chelsea as West Bromwich Albion continues to readjust to life back in the Premier League. Chelsea has a strong record at this ground, winning its last three matches here.

column3: English Premier League 2020-09-27 Manchester City vs Leicester
column7: Manchester City and Leicester City meet at Etihad Stadium. Since winning 3-1 here on the way to winning the Premier League, Leicester has lost all four times it has visited, with former star Riyad Mahrez scoring in last season's 3-1 result.

column3: English Premier League 2020-09-27 Sheffield United vs Leeds
column7: Pride is on the line in this Yorkshire Derby as Sheffield United hosts Leeds United. This is the first time that these two soccer teams have met in the Premier League since 1994, although they have met 12 times in other competitions since then.

column3: English Premier League 2020-09-27 Tottenham vs Newcastle
column7: Newcastle United visits Tottenham Hotspur Stadium a year since winning 1-0 on its first visit there. Newcastle signings Callum Wilson and Ryan Fraser were linked with Tottenham Hotspur in the summer - could they inspire a win for the Magpies?

column3: English Premier League 2020-09-27 West Ham vs Wolves
column7: Three months after winning 2-0 at London Stadium, Wolverhampton Wanderers return to East London aiming for a fifth-straight win over West Ham United. Since returning to the Premier League, Wolves has not conceded once to the Hammers.

column3: English Premier League 2020-09-28 Fulham vs Aston Villa
column7: Fulham and Aston Villa clash in the Premier League for the first time in six-and-a-half years. The pair did meet in the EFL Championship playoff final at the end of the 2017/18 season, with a Tom Cairney goal sealing a 1-0 win for Fulham.

column3: English Premier League 2020-09-28 Liverpool vs Arsenal
column7: Liverpool may be the current Premier League champion but it has already lost to Arsenal once this season, as the Gunners won the season-opening Community Shield back in August. Can Liverpool get its revenge as Mikel Arteta's men come to Anfield?

column3: English Premier League 2020-10-03 Chelsea vs Crystal Palace
column7: Chelsea and Crystal Palace clash in a London derby at Stamford Bridge. The host has strengthened in almost every area of the field over the summer, while the Eagles have finally spent some of the 50m they received for Aaron Wan-Bissaka in 2019.

column3: English Premier League 2020-10-03 Everton vs Brighton
column7: Everton, which has started the season brightly under Carlo Ancelotti, takes on Brighton & Hove Albion, whose manager Graham Potter has assembled a squad many consider capable of upsetting the odds this season.

column3: English Premier League 2020-10-03 Leeds vs Manchester City
column7: For the first time in 16 years, Leeds United welcomes Manchester City to Elland Road. This matchup will see Pep Guardiola and Marcelo Bielsa - two managers who have certainly left their mark on the beautiful game and each other - go head-to-head.

column3: English Premier League 2020-10-03 Newcastle vs Burnley
column7: Newcastle United and Burnley square off at St. James' Park, where the Magpies were humbled 3-0 by Brighton and Hove Albion in their home opener. Newcastle did bounce back from that defeat by thumping Morecambe 7-0 in the Carabao Cup, though.

column3: English Premier League 2020-10-04 Arsenal vs Sheffield United
column7: Chris Wilder's Sheffield United travels to north London to take on a rejuvenated Arsenal led by Mikel Arteta. In their first season back in the Premier League, the Blades took four points off Arsenal, including a 1-1 draw at Emirates Stadium.

column3: English Premier League 2020-10-04 Aston Villa vs Liverpool
column7: Aston Villa and Liverpool square off at Villa Park, where last season, these teams produced one of the most exciting finishes of the campaign, as Liverpool scored twice late on to overturn an early Trezeguet goal.

column3: English Premier League 2020-10-04 Leicester vs West Ham
column7: Leicester City hosts West Ham United at King Power Stadium as Brendan Rodgers' team looks to continue its good start to the season. The Hammers, meanwhile, are in the middle of an intimidating run of fixtures.

column3: English Premier League 2020-10-04 Manchester United vs Tottenham
column7: Tottenham Hotspur makes the trip to Old Trafford to take on Manchester United. Spurs has only beaten United once in its last four attempts, a 3-0 win at the Theatre of Dreams when Jose Mourinho was in the opposing dugout.

column3: English Premier League 2020-10-04 Southampton vs West Brom
column7: Southampton welcomes West Bromwich Albion back to St. Mary's for the first time since October 2017, when Sofiane Boufal scored the only goal of the game as the Saints came out on top. Just three Southampton players remain from that starting line-up.

column3: English Premier League 2020-10-04 Wolves vs Fulham
column7: Wolverhampton Wanderers does battle with Fulham, which has made a rocky start to life back in the top flight. Nuno Espirito Santo, meanwhile, has continued to bolster his side with his compatriots, meaning Wolves now has 10 Portuguese players.

column3: English Premier League 2020-10-17 Chelsea vs Southampton
column7: Chelsea resumes its Premier League campaign with the arrival of Southampton in South West London. New signing Timo Werner continues to chase his first Premier League goal for the Blues, who beat Crystal Palace 4-0 last time out.

column3: English Premier League 2020-10-17 Everton vs Liverpool
column7: Fierce rivals Everton and Liverpool meet for the second behind-closed-doors Merseyside Derby, with the Toffees flying high at the top of the table alongside the Reds. Goodison Park hosted both teams' first game of Project Restart.

column3: English Premier League 2020-10-17 Manchester City vs Arsenal
column7: Mikel Arteta returns to Manchester City, targeting another victory over his former mentor Pep Guardiola, who he knocked out of last seasons FA Cup. Arsenal, however, does not enjoy playing at Etihad Stadium, having last won here in 2015.

column3: English Premier League 2020-10-17 Newcastle vs Manchester United
column7: Steve Bruce eyes back-to-back home victories as a stuttering Manchester United visits Newcastle United. Ole Gunnar Solskjaer's team struggled at St James' Park last year, with a late Matty Longstaff goal securing an unexpected win for the Magpies.

column3: English Premier League 2020-10-18 Crystal Palace vs Brighton
column7: Crystal Palace plays Brighton and Hove Albion in the first M23 Derby of 2020. Both teams shipped four goals in their last game before the international break, though Palace has already beaten Manchester United this season.

column3: English Premier League 2020-10-18 Leicester vs Aston Villa
column7: Returning to action for the first time since stunning defending champion Liverpool 7-2, Aston Villa heads on the road to face fellow in-form team Leicester City. The Foxes have a major scalp of their own this season after beating Manchester City 5-2.

column3: English Premier League 2020-10-18 Sheffield United vs Fulham
column7: Sheffield United looks to shake off its second season syndrome as it takes on fellow struggler Fulham. The visitor has dominated this fixture in recent times, winning the last three meetings including a 5-4 victory at Bramall Lane in 2017.

column3: English Premier League 2020-10-18 Tottenham vs West Ham
column7: Tottenham Hotspur Stadium hosts a London derby as West Ham United has the unenviable task of taking on a Spurs team that humiliated Manchester United last time out. The Hammers were the first road team to beat Spurs here, though, in 2019.

column3: English Premier League 2020-10-19 Leeds vs Wolves
column7: Leeds Uniteds return to the Premier League has brought huge excitement, with Marcelo Bielsa producing positive results and performances. Having held Manchester City to a 1-1 draw last time out, can Leeds now see off Wolverhampton Wanderers?

column3: English Premier League 2020-10-19 West Brom vs Burnley
column7: West Bromwich Albion's return to the Premier League has been tough going so far, with just one point from its opening four matches. Can Slaven Bilic's team kickstart its season as fellow struggler Burnley comes to town?

column3: English Premier League 2020-10-23 Aston Villa vs Leeds
English Premier League 2020-10-24 Fulham vs Crystal Palace
column7: Roy Hodgson takes Crystal Palace on a short trip across London to face newly-promoted Fulham. Scott Parker's side has struggled to re-acclimatize to life in the Premier League, without a point in its first four games.

column3: English Premier League 2020-10-24 Liverpool vs Sheffield United
column7: Reigning champion Liverpool takes on a side which gave it plenty of problems last season in Sheffield United. Although Liverpool came away from these fixtures last year with six points, the Blades acquitted themselves well against the champion.

column3: English Premier League 2020-10-24 Manchester United vs Chelsea
column7: Manchester United and Chelsea square off as two of the Premier League's biggest teams go head-to-head once again. Chelsea's big-money signings are yet to start paying off, as the likes of Timo Werner struggle to adapt to the English game.

column3: English Premier League 2020-10-24 West Ham vs Manchester City
column7: Manchester City travels to the London Stadium to take on a West Ham United side which has started the season better than any of its fans could have expected. Pep Guardiola's side, meanwhile, has yet to hit top gear in the Premier League this season.

English Premier League 2021-05-02 Newcastle vs Arsenal
column7: Newcastle United hopes to stay away from the relegation zone when it hosts Arsenal. The Magpies are currently unbeaten in their last five matches at St. James Park, but face an Arsenal team looking to secure a European place.

column3: English Premier League 2021-05-02 Tottenham vs Sheffield United
column7: Having lost the EFL Cup final, Tottenham Hotspur resumes its league campaign with a game against already relegated Sheffield United. The Blades last trip to Tottenham back in 2019, was embroiled by a controversial VAR decision.

column3: English Premier League 2021-05-03 Burnley vs West Ham
English Premier League 2021-05-03 West Brom vs Wolves
English Premier League 2021-05-07 Leicester vs Newcastle
English Premier League 2021-05-08 Leeds vs Tottenham
column7: Leeds United hosts Tottenham Hotspur at Elland Road. Spurs sank Leeds 3-0 in London during the festive period, but may struggle at a stadium where Manchester United, Manchester City, Liverpool, Chelsea and Arsenal have all dropped points this season.

column3: English Premier League 2021-05-08 Liverpool vs Southampton
column7: Liverpool hosts Southampton hoping to keep alive its dwindling chances of finishing in the top four. The Saints have been woeful in 2021, winning just three times, with the first of those coming via a Danny Ings goal in the first week of the year.

column3: English Premier League 2021-05-08 Manchester City vs Chelsea
column7: Manchester City and Chelsea meet in what could be a preview of the upcoming UEFA Champions League final. The teams met last month at Wembley in the FA Cup semi-finals, with Thomas Tuchel trumping Pep Guardiola on that occasion.

column3: English Premier League 2021-05-08 Sheffield United vs Crystal Palace
column7: Can already-relegated Sheffield United salvage some pride against visiting Crystal Palace? Roy Hodgsons sides last trip to Bramall Lane ended in a 1-0 defeat, with John Lundstram scoring the winner for the Blades.

column3: English Premier League 2021-05-09 Arsenal vs West Brom
column7: Having both endured difficult seasons, Arsenal and West Bromwich Albion meet at Emirates Stadium. Will The Gunners suffer a continental hangover from their Europa League semi-final second leg against former manager Unai Emery?

column3: English Premier League 2021-05-09 Aston Villa vs Manchester United
column7: Manchester United travels to Villa Park chasing a third-straight league win over Aston Villa. Bruno Fernandes has scored penalties in each of the two previous victories, a 3-0 win in Birmingham last season and a 2-1 triumph at Old Trafford earlier in the campaign.

column3: English Premier League 2021-05-09 West Ham vs Everton
column7: 16 years after taking Everton to the UEFA Champions League, David Moyes aims to do the same with West Ham United as the London outfit chases a top-four finish. The Hammers snatched a 1-0 victory at Goodison Park on New Years Day.

column3: English Premier League 2021-05-09 Wolves vs Brighton
column7: Wolverhampton Wanderers have been inconsistent at Molineux with just two victories in the last nine league games there. Brighton and Hove Albion head to the West Midlands relishing its road games, having won more away than at home.

column3: English Premier League 2021-05-10 Fulham vs Burnley
column7: Relegation to the EFL Championship is almost a certainty when Fulham welcomes Burnley to Craven Cottage. These two teams couldnt be separated earlier in the season, playing out a 1-1 draw in the reverse fixture at Turf Moor.

column3: English Premier League 2021-05-11 Southampton vs Crystal Palace
column7: Two teams in the bottom half of the Premier League table go head-to-head as Southampton hosts Crystal Palace. These sides should be safe from relegation, but will want to pick up as many points as possible to end their season on a high.

column3: English Premier League 2021-05-11 Manchester United vs Leicester
column7: Manchester United hosts Leicester City in a top-four clash between two clubs with more to play for outside of the Premier League than within it, as both sides are still in with a chance of lifting trophies in other competitions.

column3: English Premier League 2021-05-12 Chelsea vs Arsenal
column7: Two huge London sides go toe-to-toe at Stamford Bridge as Chelsea prepares for a huge end to the season with 4th place still to play for as well as the FA Cup final. The last time the Blues played Arsenal, the Gunners won 3-1.

column3: English Premier League 2021-05-13 Aston Villa vs Everton
column7: Everton faces a trip to Aston Villa in the Premier League. After avoiding relegation on the final day last year, The Villains have enjoyed a successful season and look set for a top half finish, for the first time since the 2010/2011 season.

column3: English Premier League 2021-05-13 Manchester United vs Liverpool
column7: Manchester United and Liverpool clash in the latest chapter of one of soccers greatest rivalries. A win against its bitter rival is vital for Liverpool as it looks to secure a place in next seasons UEFA Champions League.

column3: English Premier League 2021-05-14 Newcastle vs Manchester City
English Premier League 2021-05-15 Brighton vs West Ham
column7: Brighton and Hove Albion looks to disrupt West Ham Uniteds push for a top-four finish on the South Coast. The Hammers had to mount two comebacks to draw 2-2 when these two teams went head-to-head in East London.

column3: English Premier League 2021-05-15 Burnley vs Leeds
column7: Leeds United travels to Burnley where a win would help Marcelo Bielsas team solidify its place in the top half of the table. The Clarets form at Turf Moor has been poor over recent months, as their last win here came at the end of January.

column3: English Premier League 2021-05-15 Southampton vs Fulham
column7: Southampton hosts Fulham on the penultimate day of the season, with Fulham already relegated. It was a rather uneventful game when the Cottagers faced Southampton last December, the two teams played out a 0-0 draw on the banks of the River Thames.

column3: English Premier League 2021-05-16 Everton vs Sheffield United
column7: Everton takes on already-relegated Sheffield United in the Premier League. Carlo Ancelottis men from Merseyside are pushing for a place in the European spots, and will need to pick up three points here to stand any chance of qualification.

column3: English Premier League 2021-05-16 West Brom vs Liverpool
column7: Sam Allardyces West Bromwich Albion hosts Liverpool at the Hawthorns with the Baggies needing a win to maintain their Premier League status. When the two sides met at Anfield, Semi Ajayi scored a late equalizer in a 1-1 draw.

column3: English Premier League 2021-05-16 Tottenham vs Wolves
column7: Tottenham Hotspur welcomes Wolverhampton Wanderers to North London. There will be a huge focus on Wolves boss Nuno Espirito Santo, the Portuguese coach is being linked with the managerial vacancy at Spurs.

column3: English Premier League 2021-05-16 Crystal Palace vs Aston Villa
column7: Crystal Palace and Aston Villa square off with both teams in a much better position than 12 months ago. Already with their Premier League status confirmed, its now a case of securing the highest possible finish before attention turns to 2021/22.

column3: English Premier League 2021-05-18 Brighton vs Manchester City
column7: Brighton and Hove Albion welcomes Pep Guardiolas Manchester City to the Amex. A dogged defensive display wasnt enough for Brighton in the reverse fixture, where a Phil Foden strike helped City secure the win at Etihad Stadium.

column3: English Premier League 2021-05-18 Chelsea vs Leicester
column7: Leicester City and Chelsea clash in a game which could have major implications in the race for a top four finish. This is the second time in three days the two teams have gone head-to-head after facing each other in Saturdays FA Cup Final.

column3: English Premier League 2021-05-18 Manchester United vs Fulham
column7: Relegated Fulham looks to salvage some pride against Manchester United at Old Trafford. Striker Edinson Cavani, who has recently signed a contract extension, scored during Uniteds 2-1 win at Craven Cottage last January.

column3: English Premier League 2021-05-18 Southampton vs Leeds
column7: Leeds United takes the long journey down to St. Marys, completing Southamptons congested run of three games in the space of a week. The reverse fixture at Elland Road saw the Yorkshire side win comprehensively with a 3-0 victory.

column3: English Premier League 2021-05-19 Burnley vs Liverpool
column7: Turf Moor hosts its first fans of the campaign in Burnleys final home game of the season against Liverpool. The Reds still have a chance of qualifying for next seasons UEFA Champions League - a win will give a key boost before the final matchday.

column3: English Premier League 2021-05-19 Crystal Palace vs Arsenal
column7: Arsenal has come to loathe the sight of Crystal Palace, having not defeated the Eagles since 2018. Roy Hodgson has already assured Palace of top-flight football next year, but the Gooners must get a result as it strives for continental football.

column3: English Premier League 2021-05-19 Everton vs Wolves
column7: Evertons quest for European soccer continues as Carlo Ancelottis team hosts Wolverhampton Wanderers at Goodison Park. Michael Keanes powerful late header was the difference when the teams met earlier in the season in a 2-1 win.

column3: English Premier League 2021-05-19 Newcastle vs Sheffield United
column7: Sheffield United faces Newcastle United at St. James Park. A second half penalty from Blades legend Billy Sharp separated the two teams in the reverse fixture, will there a be a similar result in the North East?

column3: English Premier League 2021-05-19 Tottenham vs Aston Villa
column7: Aston Villa takes on Tottenham Hotspur in North London. While the UEFA Champions League is maybe a step too far for Spurs, they could still play European soccer next season by securing a place in the UEFA Europa League.

column3: English Premier League 2021-05-19 West Brom vs West Ham
column7: West Bromwich Albion plays its penultimate game in the Premier League against West Ham United before heading back to the EFL Championship. The Hammers UEFA Champions League ambitions are hanging by a thread after three defeats in their last five.

column3: English Premier League 2021-05-23 Arsenal vs Brighton
column7: Arsenal hosts Brighton and Hove Albion on the final day as fans make their long awaited return to Emirates Stadium. The Seagulls were victorious here 18 months ago and have a decent record against the Gunners in recent years.

column3: English Premier League 2021-05-23 Aston Villa vs Chelsea
column7: Chelsea plays its final game before next weeks UEFA Champions League final. Aston Villas England hopefuls have one final audition to make Gareth Southgates EURO squad, while the Blues will want to head into next weeks showpiece in winning form.

column3: English Premier League 2021-05-23 Fulham vs Newcastle
column7: Fulham welcomes Newcastle United to Craven Cottage for the final game of the Premier League season. Scott Parkers men have already been relegated after teams like Newcastle hit a purple patch of form to pull away at the back end of the season.

column3: English Premier League 2021-05-23 Leeds vs West Brom
column7: Leeds United will play in front of its fans for the first time this season, as West Brom turns up to Elland Road before returning to the EFL Championship next season. Leeds United won the reverse fixture 5-0 at the Hawthorns back in December.

column3: English Premier League 2021-05-23 Leicester vs Tottenham
column7: Leicester City could seal a place in next seasons Champions League with a win over Tottenham Hotspur on the final day. Foxes boss Brendan Rodgers has been linked with the vacant managers role at Spurs, could this be his final game with Leicester?

column3: English Premier League 2021-05-23 Liverpool vs Crystal Palace
column7: Liverpools challenging season reaches its climax at Anfield as former Reds boss Roy Hodgson leads Crystal Palace in what could be the final game of his managerial career. Hodgsons career began in Sweden in 1976 and spans over 1200 games to date.

column3: English Premier League 2021-05-23 Manchester City vs Everton
column7: Fernandinho and Sergio Aguero will lift the Premier League title together in front of fans, but not before Manchester Citys home clash with Everton at the Etihad. The Toffees are still in the running for the UEFA Europa League.

column3: English Premier League 2021-05-23 Sheffield United vs Burnley
column7: Sheffield United, headed back to the second tier of English football, welcomes Burnley to Bramall Lane for the last game of the season. When the two met at Turf Moor in December, it was captain Ben Mee whose goal was the difference between the teams.

column3: English Premier League 2021-05-23 West Ham vs Southampton
column7: With just one game left of the season, West Ham United takes on Southampton with all eyes on the Hammers European aspirations. Its been an unbelievable season for David Moyes men, but anything less than a win could have catastrophic consequences.

column3: English Premier League 2021-05-23 Wolves vs Manchester United
column7: One game out from the UEFA Europa League final, Manchester United heads to Wolverhampton Wanderers on the final day of the Premier League season. United have enjoyed an impressive campaign, finishing second under Ole Gunnar Solskjaer.

column3: English Premier League 2021-08-13 Brentford vs Arsenal
column7: Premier League newcomer Brentford plays its first-ever game in the division against Arsenal with the Gunners keen to start off on a positive note, after finishing last season 8th and missing out on European soccer for the first time since 1996.

column3: English Premier League 2021-08-14 Burnley vs Brighton
column7: After finishing 17th and 16th last season respectively, both Burnley and Brighton and Hove Albion will both be aiming to push on in the new campaign. They begin their seasons at Turf Moor, where last season they shared the points in a 1-1 draw.

column3: English Premier League 2021-08-14 Chelsea vs Crystal Palace
column7: Last seasons UEFA Champions League winner Chelsea welcomes Crystal Palace to Stamford Bridge on the opening day of the new campaign. The Eagles last won here in April 2017 but have now lost seven straight games against the Blues.

column3: English Premier League 2021-08-14 Everton vs Southampton
column7: After Carlo Ancelottis shock return to Real Madrid, Everton begins yet another season under new guidance. The Toffees home form was poor last season, can Southampton capitalize to win a league game at Goodison Park for the first time since 1997?

column3: English Premier League 2021-08-14 Leicester vs Wolves
column7: Leicester City returns to King Power Stadium for the first time since its loss to Tottenham Hotspur last season which saw it miss out on UEFA Champions League soccer. Its opponent, Wolverhampton Wanderers, starts a new era under Bruno Lage.

column3: English Premier League 2021-08-14 Manchester United vs Leeds
column7: Fierce rivals Manchester United and Leeds United clash in the most eye-watering tie of the opening weekend. It was an eight-goal thriller when they met at Old Trafford last year with United winning 6-2, but Leeds held it to a goalless draw in April.

column3: English Premier League 2021-08-14 Norwich vs Liverpool
column7: Two years after opening its last Premier League campaign at Anfield, Norwich City hosts Liverpool ahead of a challenging run of fixtures. The Reds are 14 games unbeaten against the Canaries and have not lost an opening day fixture since 2012.

column3: English Premier League 2021-08-14 Watford vs Aston Villa
column7: Vicarage Road is yet again a Premier League destination as Aston Villa visit Watford on the opening weekend. Troy Deeney and Ismaila Sarr wrapped up a 3-0 victory for the Hornets in the last meeting in Hertfordshire back in 2019.

English Premier League 2021-10-16 Aston Villa vs Wolves
column7: Aston Villa hosts Wolverhampton Wanderers at Villa Park. The last three meetings have only seen two goals in total - which is the same as the number of red cards, with each team getting one in the same game.

column3: English Premier League 2021-10-16 Brentford vs Chelsea
English Premier League 2021-10-16 Leicester vs Manchester United
column7: Leicester City hosts Manchester United at King Power Stadium. The Red Devils have lost two successive games against Leicester in the FA Cup final and Premier League respectively, and look to exact its revenge against The Foxes this time out.

column3: English Premier League 2021-10-16 Manchester City vs Burnley
column7: Reigning champion Manchester City hosts Sean Dyches Burnley at Etihad Stadium. City boasts an excellent record against its opponent, having conceded only two league goals to Burnley since 2018.

column3: English Premier League 2021-10-16 Norwich vs Brighton
column7: Newly-promoted Norwich City clashes with Brighton and Hove Albion at Carrow Road. Both sides will be vying for a hugely important win, as they bid to extend their stay in the Premier League by another year.

column3: English Premier League 2021-10-16 Southampton vs Leeds
column7: Southampton lines up against Leeds United at St Marys Stadium. Southampton has not recorded a triumph over Leeds since March 2012, which came in the form of a narrow 1-0 victory in Englands second division.

column3: English Premier League 2021-10-16 Watford vs Liverpool
column7: Liverpool travels to Vicarage Road, where it faces newly promoted Watford in the Premier League. The Hornets sacked Xisco Munoz after a defeat to Leeds United, and Claudio Ranieri will be the man in charge against the Reds.

column3: English Premier League 2021-10-17 Everton vs West Ham
English Premier League 2021-10-17 Newcastle vs Tottenham
English Premier League 2021-10-18 Arsenal vs Crystal Palace
English Premier League 2021-10-22 Arsenal vs Aston Villa
column7: Mikel Artetas Arsenal welcomes Aston Villa to Emirates Stadium. The Gunners last tasted victory against its opponents in 2019, with Villa having won the last three consecutive games between the sides, including a 3-0 triumph in north London.

column3: English Premier League 2021-10-23 Brighton vs Manchester City
column7: Pep Guardiolas Manchester City travels to Amex Stadium, where Brighton and Hove Albion lay in wait. The champions will be out to avenge its shock defeat to the Seagulls last season, where a 2-0 lead was surrendered during a stunning 3-2 loss.

column3: English Premier League 2021-10-23 Chelsea vs Norwich
column7: Chelsea welcomes newly promoted Norwich City to Stamford Bridge for a Premier League showdown. The Canaries have not tasted victory over the Blues since 1994, and will be keen to stage a big upset in London.

column3: English Premier League 2021-10-23 Crystal Palace vs Newcastle
column7: Patrick Vieiras Crystal Palace host Newcastle United in the Premier League at Selhurst Park. The Magpies were beaten by Tottenham Hotspur in the first game since the clubs takeover. Can they turn things around against the Eagles?

column3: English Premier League 2021-10-23 Everton vs Watford
column7: Watford pays a visit to Goodison Park, where it faces Everton in the Premier League. Claudio Ranieris time in charge of Watford started with a mauling by Liverpool. Will it be another sobering experience against a team from Merseyside?

column3: English Premier League 2021-10-23 Leeds vs Wolves
column7: All the action as Leeds United hosts Wolverhampton Wanderers at Elland Road. Marcelo Bielsas Leeds is hovering above the Premier League relegation zone after a loss to Southampton, while Wolves beat Aston Villa in thrilling style last time out.

column3: English Premier League 2021-10-23 Southampton vs Burnley
column7: Southampton welcomes Sean Dyches Burnley to St Marys Stadium. With both teams rooted firmly in the bottom half of the Premier League table, neither will be wanting to settle for anything less than three points.

column3: English Premier League 2021-10-24 Brentford vs Leicester
column7: All the action as Brentford hosts Leicester City in the Premier League. The away side travels to London looking to build on a win over Manchester United, while the Bees look to bounce back from a narrow home defeat to Chelsea.

column3: English Premier League 2021-10-24 Manchester United vs Liverpool
column7: Two of Englands biggest teams go head-to-head as Manchester United hosts Liverpool. With the likes of Jadon Sancho and Cristiano Ronaldo to call upon, United will hope for a first win over the Reds in the Premier League since 2018.

column3: English Premier League 2021-10-24 West Ham vs Tottenham
column7: West Ham United hosts Tottenham Hotspur in a London derby. Nuno Espirito Santos Spurs side travels to London Stadium with Harry Kane looking to build on his first Premier League goal of the season against Newcastle United last weekend.

column7: The Premier is back! After a few eternal weeks without club football, the best league in the world is here. Crystal Palace and Arsenal are in charge of kicking off this new season. A high-level match between two Premier League classics!

column3: English Premier League 2022-08-06 Fulham vs Liverpool
column7: Jrgen Klopp's Liverpool, who arrive at the event after winning the Community Shield, the first title of the course, opens this Premier League season by visiting Craven Cottage, where the newly promoted, although classic in the competition, awaits them, Fulham . As classic as its old stadium.

column3: English Premier League 2022-08-06 Bournemouth vs Aston Villa
column7: Bournemouth and Aston Villa begin their participation in the current edition of the Premier League measuring forces at the Vitality Stadium. Curiously, Bournemouth's premiere in the Premier was against the villains in 2015.

column3: English Premier League 2022-08-06 Leeds vs Wolves
column7: Leeds United, who suffered excessively last season to achieve permanence, and Wolverhampton begin their journey in the new season of the Premier League facing each other at Elland Road. Wolves ended last season on a losing run on the road and haven't won away from home in the league since March.

column3: English Premier League 2022-08-06 Tottenham vs Southampton
column7: Tottenham faces an important season, in which they will participate in the Champions League, and they do so in the domestic championship making their debut against Southampton at home. The duo formed by Kane (11) and Son (10) have 21 goals against Soton. One of the favorite prey of the Spurs offensive tandem.

column3: English Premier League 2022-08-06 Everton vs Chelsea
column7: Chelsea opens fire this Premier League season at Goodison Park to face off against Everton who want to leave behind what they suffered last season. The last four visits of the blues to the toffee stadium. This is the Londoners' worst current run with any English club.

column3: English Premier League 2022-08-06 Newcastle vs Nottingham Forest
column7: The historic Nottingham Forest, which returns to the Premier League this season since relegation from the top English competition in 1999, debuts against the always difficult Newcastle at St James Park, who also have Forest as one of their favorite victims.

column3: English Premier League 2022-08-07 Leicester vs Brentford
column7: Leicester and Brentford meet at the King Power Stadium on the first day of the new Premier League season. Vardy, the top scorer in the history of the Foxes, is only 17 goals away from 150 goals and thus enters the top-10 of the Premier's top scorers.

column3: English Premier League 2022-08-07 Manchester United vs Brighton
column7: Manchester United need to return to the elite of the Premier League after a disastrous season in which they had to settle for sixth place and with empty hands of titles. Their debut is this season, at Old Trafford against Brighton, a rival that still doesn't know what it's like to win at the Theater of Dreams. Will the streak continue?

column3: English Premier League 2022-08-07 West Ham vs Manchester City
column7: Manchester City, led by Erling-Braut Haaland, begins the defense of its Premier League title won last season at the London Stadium, where a West Ham team that wants to fight for Europe awaits. City are undefeated in their last 13 Premier games with the hammers (W10 and D3), and only against Fulham (14) are they on a longer unbeaten streak between teams in the 2022/23 Premier!

column7: The England classic is here! Manchester United and Liverpool face each other in a real match in which each team goes through very different dynamics. The Red Devils still do not know the victory in this Premier League and come from a blushing 4-0 against Brentford. For its part, Jurgen Klopp's team, without Darwin Nuez, arrives at Old Trafford after drawing against Crystal Palace last day.

column3: English Premier League 2022-08-27 Arsenal vs Fulham
column7: Arsenal wants to continue the streak, they already have three of three, in the second London derby of this campaign. Fulham are bad at Gunners. They have only added three wins out of 30 duels against their neighbors and never as visitors.

column3: English Premier League 2022-08-27 Brentford vs Everton
English Premier League 2022-08-27 Brighton vs Leeds
English Premier League 2022-08-27 Chelsea vs Leicester
column7: Although Leicester are not traditionally good at Chelsea at Stamford Bridge, the Foxes have chased great results in their recent visits to the blue fiefdom, both in the FA Cup and the Premier League.

column3: English Premier League 2022-08-27 Liverpool vs Bournemouth
column7: Bournemouth have never won at Anfield Road. In fact, they have only managed one goal in their last five games against a much-needed Liverpool side. And it is that the Reds have not yet won this season in the Premier.

column3: English Premier League 2022-08-27 Manchester City vs Crystal Palace
column7: Crystal Palace is one of the great killers of the Premier. The glaziers tend to score quite a few times at the home of the Big-6 teams. Not surprisingly, they have beaten City at the Etihad in 2018 and 2021.

column3: English Premier League 2022-08-27 Southampton vs Manchester United
column7: Southampton hosts Cristiano Ronaldo's Manchester United, and also Casemiro's, on matchday four of the Premier League. New litmus test for the Red Devils, who have no margin for error if they want to stick to the top of the rankings.
